<br>
Well, it was the case a while ago.  NPCs have an &quot;awareness&quot; list of people in range and KOS, but not close enough to be agged yet.<br>
<br>
It was a common thing that a rogue could pull a mob (we'll say an Orc who's KOS to all) then evade.  The mob would forget about the rogue to a point where the rogue's aggro would drop BELOW the awareness list.  The mob would then attack someone else.  Griefer tactics.  I know--it's happened to me.  I evaded once and dropped Dwigus Lowater onto my entire group who hadn't started the combat yet.  We lost 5 of the 8 we sent into that combat because of that...<br>
<br>
